This statement by the President of the United States marks the 16th anniversary of the genocide in Rwanda. The President honors those who were lost and acknowledges the pain and trauma experienced by survivors. The statement emphasizes the need to prevent mass atrocities and genocide, stating that it is not enough to simply say "never again." The United States reaffirms its commitment to its partnership with Rwanda and pledges to support efforts for sustainable development, respect for human rights, and peace in the region.